text.tspan: Bret's Character Template
Bret.Stateham@microsoft.com
Get the latest version from http://aka.ms/isct or http://aka.ms/isctzip
Created using InkScape. Get a free copy here: http://aka.ms/isdl
Leave the "Wireframe" layer untouched as a reference
Based on (with modification) Chris Hildebrand's excellent article:
http://aka.ms/chgc
Modify the shapes on the Character layer for your character
Arms and legs have been grouped in sections (Whole, Upper, Lower)
to make it easier to move them. Double click on a group to enter it
and modify its parts
When exporting, lock all layers except "Bounding Box", then select
all elements on the "Bounding Box" layer (there is only
a single 512x512 square. Then in the Export Dialog make
sure to turn OFF the "Hide all except selected" checkbox.
